{"type":"message","id":"35784884","parentId":"624e615c","timestamp":"2026-07-08T09:15:25.136Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00219b0427a349f9bb39cbb9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \"264468965\" image \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\" \"Your middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\n\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\n\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\n\nMiddle managers are caught between:\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\n\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\n→ Tool selection and procurement\n→ Training and upskilling programs\n→ Change management across teams\n→ Security and compliance concerns\n→ Productivity expectations from above\n\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\n\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\n\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\n\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\n\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\n\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\n\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"/data/workspace/skills/linkedin-publish/li-post.sh \\\"264468965\\\" image \\\"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\\\" \\\"Your middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\\n\\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\\n\\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\\n\\nMiddle managers are caught between:\\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\\n\\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\\n→ Tool selection and procurement\\n→ Training and upskilling programs\\n→ Change management across teams\\n→ Security and compliance concerns\\n→ Productivity expectations from above\\n\\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\\n\\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\\n\\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\\n\\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\\n\\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\\n\\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\\n\\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783502116784,"responseId":"JRVOapSWPL-S6dgPqeLdoAI"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2235dc1c","parentId":"35784884","timestamp":"2026-07-08T09:15:29.213Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00219b0427a349f9bb39cbb9","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480550112566628352/\nDISPLAY_NAME: Andrii Bidochko\nCHARS: 1331"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":4045,"aggregated":"OK: https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480550112566628352/\nDISPLAY_NAME: Andrii Bidochko\nCHARS: 1331","cwd":"/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1783502129210}}
{"type":"message","id":"20bcef10","parentId":"2235dc1c","timestamp":"2026-07-08T09:15:40.762Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9318ba3e5a8049d69e4ae2d1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-08-your-middle-managers-are-drowning.md","content":"# Your middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\n\n**Published:** 2026-07-08T09:15:00Z\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480550112566628352/\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7480550112566628352\n**Format:** image\n**Characters:** 1331\n**Pillar:** (unknown)\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\n\n## Post Body\n\nYour middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\n\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\n\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\n\nMiddle managers are caught between:\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\n\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\n→ Tool selection and procurement\n→ Training and upskilling programs\n→ Change management across teams\n→ Security and compliance concerns\n→ Productivity expectations from above\n\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\n\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\n\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\n\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\n\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\n\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\n\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\n\n## Performance\n\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\n\n- **Impressions:** —\n- **Reactions:** —\n- **Comments:** —\n- **Shares:** —\n- **Last checked:** —\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/posts/2026-07-08-your-middle-managers-are-drowning.md\", \"content\": \"# Your middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\\n\\n**Published:** 2026-07-08T09:15:00Z\\n**LinkedIn URL:** https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:share:7480550112566628352/\\n**Post URN:** urn:li:share:7480550112566628352\\n**Format:** image\\n**Characters:** 1331\\n**Pillar:** (unknown)\\n**Image:** /data/workspace/social/linkedin/264468965/images/middle-managers-1783494572.png\\n\\n## Post Body\\n\\nYour middle managers are drowning in AI adoption. And nobody's talking about it.\\n\\nNew HBR research found something uncomfortable. Most companies treat AI rollout as a tech project. IT installs it. C-suite celebrates it. Headcount reduction gets mentioned.\\n\\nBut there's a layer in the middle getting crushed.\\n\\nMiddle managers are caught between:\\n• Executives demanding AI transformation NOW\\n• Teams who need training, guidance, and support\\n• Zero formal playbook on how to actually do this\\n\\nThey're not just managing people anymore. They're managing:\\n→ Tool selection and procurement\\n→ Training and upskilling programs\\n→ Change management across teams\\n→ Security and compliance concerns\\n→ Productivity expectations from above\\n\\nAll while doing their actual jobs.\\n\\nHere's the hard truth most leaders miss:\\nAI doesn't eliminate middle management — it makes it harder.\\n\\nThe people who used to just execute now have to translate between human needs and AI capabilities. That's a new skill. And nobody taught it to them.\\n\\nIf you're a middle manager feeling this — you're not failing. The playbook just doesn't exist yet.\\n\\nAnd if you're a leader? Check in on your middle layer before you lose them.\\n\\nWhat's actually helping your managers adapt?\\n\\n#Leadership #AIAdoption #MiddleManagement #ChangeManagement #FutureOfWork\\n\\n## Performance\\n\\n*(populated later by linkedin-analytics)*\\n\\n- **Impressions:** —\\n- **Reactions:** —\\n- **Comments:** —\\n- **Shares:** —\\n- **Last checked:** —\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"vertex_ai/zai-org/glm-5-maas","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1783502129224,"responseId":"MhVOaqWKAYqM6dgPkLuekAM"}}
